{
  "stem": "26142.13",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And the lines were weak.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "So they wanted to put in heavier lines.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And it had to be done in  a very rushed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And so they, they took in some-- I don't remember how many thousand, maybe four, five, maybe a thousand of, of us boys to, to change the lines.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And we thought, we thought that this was a very important job that has to be done.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And already by-- this was 1943-- already by then, I, I think the, the war, the war started to tilt in favor of the Allies.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And we were hoping that, that very soon, very soon, it, it will end.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "But sadly that it, it lasted for another, for almost, almost two years.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And we worked there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I remember Yom Kippur, which, which usually comes out either the end of September or the beginning of October.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "We worked on that, on that railroad line.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "That was backbreaking labor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "But we weren't hungry then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "In hungry, our commander was a decent person.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And, and he saw to it that we got enough food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We did very important work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And he said, he said that we have, if you, you want good work, you have to feed the people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "So we did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And, and people that had relatives in September, October, people that had relatives were able to, to get a-- for the high holiday, for Yom Kippur-- a 24-hour, what they called in Hungarian, [HUNGARIAN] which meant that you can get away for 24 hours from your, from your your work.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So since my brother Eliezer lived in Debrecen, and [INAUDIBLE], it was only a couple hours by train.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I figured I will go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we will be together for the high holiday.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
